{
  "texts": [
    "However, this is contradictory to other findings, such as those of Nay et al. (2023) and Blair-Stanek et al. (2023), which used zero-shot performance as a baseline.",
    "Nay et al. (2023) also explored chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting and few-shot prompting, and combined these approaches.",
    "CoT prompting involves asking an LLM to \"think step-by-step\", which Kojima et al. (2023) previously found to improve performance (though not specifically in legal tasks).",
    "Nay et al. (2023) found that CoT only improved the results for GPT-4 and that providing relevant legal texts in the prompts moderately improved the results.",
    "Few-shot prompting led to better results for GPT-4 but not for other models."
  ]
}